<item>
            <title>[JDK-8286581] Make Java process DPI Aware if sun.java2d.dpiaware property is set</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8286581</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The &amp;#39;sun.java2d.dpiaware&amp;#39; property controlled whether Java tried to declare itself DPI Aware for Windows. Setting this property didn&amp;#39;t work after dpiaware flag was added to the application manifest.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It doesn&amp;#39;t work now because Java launchers are Per-Monitor v2 DPI Aware via the application manifest.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Thus, we need to make sure that when sun.java2d.dpiaware is set to true we have Java process DPI awareness set to Per-Monitor v2 DPI Aware to match what is the manifest file.</description>
